    102          /**
    103           *  @brief      Lock a Mutex or wait until it gets freed
    104           *  @details    This function will perform a Mutex lock: if the Mutex is already in use by another thread
    105           *              execution will be suspended until Mutex will be released; embOS shall switch to the thread which
    106           *              locked the Mutex in order to complete execution and release it.
    107           *  @note       Check that all call to OsServices__MutexLock() in a thread will be completed
    108           *              with a call to OsServices__MutexRelease()
    109           *
    110           *  @param      mutex_ptr - Pointer to a mutex variable to lock
    111           */

